This request is intended to address the problem on confluence.atlassian.com where documentation search results are cluttered by hits from spaces that are not relevant to the vast majority of searchers. For example, all anonymous visitors looking for install assistance for Confluence will see results from the public test space and also many duplicates returned from archival spaces for older versions of Confluence. In particular, a page is often returned 3 times from the Confluence 2.7, 2,6 and 2.5 spaces. This is unprofessional for new users to see and generally makes search less useful. 

A solution is to add an administrative option where anonymous searches by default only search a manually selected list of spaces. This will allow technical writers to choose the latest documentation spaces and exclude rarely used public spaces, with the goal of making the default searches more accurate for anyone looking for product documentation.
